1
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:16,067
She's not like this before.

2
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:18,133
She loves our children so much.

3
00:00:18,267 --> 00:00:21,500
That's why she's changed
into a horrible person

4
00:00:21,633 --> 00:00:22,733
and taken revenge
because she's in pain.

5
00:00:22,867 --> 00:00:26,200
But it's wrong to take it out
on someone innocent.

6
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:29,000
My sister didn't do
anything wrong.

7
00:00:30,067 --> 00:00:31,867
- Mom!
- Aunt Amanda!

8
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Get out of here!

9
00:00:33,133 --> 00:00:35,033
You have to go,
or you'll get hurt too!

10
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:37,000
- Mom!
-No, Mom. We're not leaving you.

11
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:38,267
Get out of the way!

12
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:39,533
- Mom, you have to stop this!
- Get out of the way!

13
00:00:39,667 --> 00:00:42,967
You have to stop!
Angelo won't like this!

14
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:43,967
Please, stop!

15
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:45,533
I won't let you be happy!

16
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:48,300
- You can't be happy!
- Stop!

17
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:50,867
Red! No!

18
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:51,967
No!

19
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:58,367
I'm sorry.

20
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:02,067
I had no idea about what
she's been doing.

21
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:03,800
What kind of husband am I?

22
00:01:03,933 --> 00:01:06,267
Dad, don't be too hard
on yourself.

23
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:10,867
She's determined to hide
what she's been doing.

24
00:01:11,033 --> 00:01:13,000
She doesn't want us to know.

25
00:01:13,133 --> 00:01:16,100
Eden, we've done you a lot
of wrong things.

26
00:01:16,233 --> 00:01:20,767
We took you away from your mom
and your child.

27
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:22,700
She lost a lot of blood.

28
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:24,533
She needs you right now.

29
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:27,300
You have to stay by her side.

30
00:01:27,433 --> 00:01:29,567
She wants to talk to you.

31
00:01:31,167 --> 00:01:34,133
Please forgive me, Amanda.

32
00:01:34,267 --> 00:01:35,733
Red was right.

33
00:01:35,867 --> 00:01:40,300
I looked for someone to blame.

34
00:01:40,467 --> 00:01:43,800
I couldn't bear to lose my son.

35
00:01:43,933 --> 00:01:48,033
I was blinded by my anger.

36
00:01:48,167 --> 00:01:50,733
It's all my fault.

37
00:01:50,867 --> 00:01:54,100
Amanda, I want to ask you
a favor.

38
00:01:54,233 --> 00:01:58,933
Take care of our children,
Amanda.

39
00:01:59,067 --> 00:02:02,067
- I will take care of them.
- Promise me...

40
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:04,300
You will take care of them.

41
00:02:04,433 --> 00:02:09,533
Rina, all your pain will be
wiped away.

42
00:02:09,667 --> 00:02:11,300
You can rest now.

43
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:15,533
I didn't get to protect your mom
against herself.

44
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:17,300
And she ended up hurting you
and Eden.

45
00:02:17,433 --> 00:02:18,333
She's gone now.

46
00:02:18,467 --> 00:02:19,700
I should have died too.

47
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:21,367
I don't deserve to be here.

48
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:23,233
- No, Dad.
- After I failed, Red.

49
00:02:23,367 --> 00:02:25,733
- I failed.
- Dad, I don't want to lose you.

50
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:28,067
I need you.

51
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:29,800
Your grandchild needs you.

52
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:23,033
I was blinded by my anger
and pain, Amanda.

53
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:35,167
Please, forgive me.

54
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:42,700
Take care of our children,
Amanda.

55
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:49,100
You're more deserving
to be loved by our grandchild.

56
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:29,333
My mom is with my brother now.

57
00:07:37,633 --> 00:07:39,433
Bye, Mom.

58
00:07:41,333 --> 00:07:43,400
Bye, Angelo.

59
00:07:46,533 --> 00:07:49,300
May you both be at peace.

60
00:08:26,867 --> 00:08:28,967
Chloe's sleeping now.

61
00:08:32,767 --> 00:08:34,200
Red...

62
00:08:35,633 --> 00:08:38,200
I know you're still grieving.

63
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:44,833
I've been too busy
since we got Chloe back.

64
00:08:44,967 --> 00:08:49,700
But I want you to know
I'm always here for you.

65
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:58,033
I'm still thinking about Mom.

66
00:09:00,167 --> 00:09:02,100
I don't understand.

67
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:07,067
No matter how many times
she hurt us...

68
00:09:08,233 --> 00:09:10,900
Even if she took our baby away
from us...

69
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:14,267
Even when she almost
killed us...

70
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:16,167
Red.

71
00:09:21,767 --> 00:09:23,767
I still love her so much.

72
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,500
I miss her so much.

73
00:09:34,267 --> 00:09:40,800
I wish that all of this
didn't happen.

74
00:09:43,367 --> 00:09:46,000
I wish she learned to forgive.

75
00:09:49,433 --> 00:09:51,467
I wish she had focused
on her love for me

76
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,667
instead of her anger.

77
00:09:58,267 --> 00:10:02,567
If she did, we would have been
complete.

78
00:10:02,733 --> 00:10:04,967
She would still be here with us.

79
00:10:11,567 --> 00:10:12,933
Red...

80
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:20,333
Don't hide what you feel for
your mom from me.

81
00:10:21,367 --> 00:10:24,233
I won't get mad.

82
00:10:24,367 --> 00:10:26,400
I've forgiven her.

83
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:32,867
And it's not wrong
to love her still.

84
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:36,633
Because she's your mom.

85
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:41,900
And it only means
you're a good son.

86
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:47,700
And I know you will be
a great father to our daughter.

87
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:57,867
We can't change
what's been done.

88
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:04,300
And we can't bring back
the people we've lost.

89
00:11:07,267 --> 00:11:09,300
But...

90
00:11:11,167 --> 00:11:17,133
We can still make up for
everything we've been through.

91
00:11:19,633 --> 00:11:25,400
As long we stay happy and heal
ourselves from all this pain.

92
00:11:25,533 --> 00:11:28,533
While we're building
our own family.

93
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:37,267
I don't want to do anything else
but make you happy.

94
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:40,100
You and Chloe.

95
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:19,567
I will never forget
all the good things

96
00:12:19,700 --> 00:12:22,633
you've done for me, Lucho.

97
00:12:24,100 --> 00:12:32,333
You gave me a new life,
new strength, and new courage.

98
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:37,733
He's been generous to Red
and me, too.

99
00:12:40,167 --> 00:12:45,833
Although he did some bad things,

100
00:12:45,967 --> 00:12:49,533
he showed you how much
he love you, Amanda.

101
00:13:02,433 --> 00:13:04,833
Thank you, Lucho.

102
00:13:07,233 --> 00:13:12,667
Thank you so much
for loving me...

103
00:13:14,767 --> 00:13:18,000
and my family.

104
00:13:22,300 --> 00:13:27,667
I want to start a new life
with my family

105
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:31,300
that's been reunited
because of you.

106
00:13:40,533 --> 00:13:42,767
Lucho...

107
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:53,500
You will always be in my heart,
even though you're already gone.

108
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,267
Chloe!

109
00:14:23,567 --> 00:14:25,633
I need to check on Chloe.

110
00:14:25,767 --> 00:14:26,633
Yen.

111
00:14:26,767 --> 00:14:27,967
Chloe!

112
00:14:29,233 --> 00:14:30,867
Yen.

113
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:35,067
Red, I thought my dream
was real.

114
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:38,000
I thought someone
had taken Chloe from us.

115
00:14:40,933 --> 00:14:43,633
Sometimes I can't
forgive myself.

116
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:47,500
I should have known
where she was.

117
00:14:47,633 --> 00:14:48,667
I'm her mom.

118
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:51,500
I should have known what
was going on with her.

119
00:14:51,633 --> 00:14:57,400
I shouldn't have given up on her
when they told me she was gone.

120
00:14:57,533 --> 00:15:00,433
I should have kept looking.

121
00:15:04,633 --> 00:15:09,667
You are her mother,
but you're not God.

122
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:12,967
I know you're trying
to handle everything.

123
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:18,467
But you will fail sometimes.

124
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,333
And that's okay.

125
00:15:21,533 --> 00:15:24,300
It won't make you less
of a mother

126
00:15:24,433 --> 00:15:26,600
because of a few mistakes.

127
00:15:27,933 --> 00:15:30,700
Just like me,
I'm her parent too.

128
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:33,533
And I'm not perfect either.

129
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,700
That's why we're here.
To help each other.

130
00:15:37,833 --> 00:15:41,500
So we could raise her properly.

131
00:15:41,633 --> 00:15:44,333
Red, don't leave us, okay?

132
00:15:45,367 --> 00:15:47,567
Never.

133
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:51,400
I know you will never
abandon our child, either.

134
00:15:53,033 --> 00:15:57,133
As you said, we can't
take back the past.

135
00:15:58,233 --> 00:16:01,233
But you know what, Yen?
I'm confident.

136
00:16:01,367 --> 00:16:02,867
Now that we have Chloe back,

137
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:07,667
I know you will be
the best mom for her.

138
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:14,167
Aren't we going to lose her
again?

139
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:16,467
It won't happen again.

140
00:16:22,167 --> 00:16:24,200
It's just a dream, okay?

141
00:16:28,533 --> 00:16:30,467
Thank you, Red.

142
00:16:40,767 --> 00:16:43,600
I can stare at her all day.

143
00:16:45,167 --> 00:16:46,367
Me, too.

144
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:48,533
I want to wake her up
to see her beautiful eyes.

145
00:16:48,667 --> 00:16:50,967
Don't wake her up!

146
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:53,867
She just fell asleep.
Don't bother her.

147
00:16:56,233 --> 00:16:57,533
Don't worry.

148
00:16:57,667 --> 00:17:03,300
We'll make up for all the times
she's not with us.

149
00:17:03,433 --> 00:17:06,367
We'll fill her
with our love.

150
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:11,767
She'll forget all the days
we're not with her.

151
00:17:12,900 --> 00:17:16,700
And we will never lose
her again.

152
00:17:22,133 --> 00:17:23,333
Yen?

153
00:17:24,967 --> 00:17:26,800
Mom.

154
00:17:36,267 --> 00:17:39,100
Wow, you're smiling.

155
00:17:39,233 --> 00:17:42,200
Of course, I'm so happy
right now.

156
00:17:42,333 --> 00:17:44,700
Because we're complete now.

157
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:48,500
You, Red, and Chloe are here.

158
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,367
Amanda.

159
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:55,633
- Yes?
- The police officers are here.

160
00:17:55,767 --> 00:17:57,867
What can I do for you?

161
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:02,300
We're investigating
your husband's illegal business.

162
00:18:02,433 --> 00:18:04,767
And we're trying to find out
if you have something to do

163
00:18:04,900 --> 00:18:07,133
with his criminal activities.

164
00:18:08,767 --> 00:18:11,633
You have to come with us
to the precinct for questioning.

165
00:18:13,233 --> 00:18:15,033
Okay, I'll go with you.

166
00:18:15,167 --> 00:18:16,833
Stay here.

167
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:35,700
Everything's okay now.

168
00:18:35,833 --> 00:18:37,133
What?

169
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:44,833
My lawyer accompanied me
to the precinct to explain

170
00:18:44,967 --> 00:18:48,867
that I had nothing to do
with Lucho's illegal business.

171
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:50,833
Thank God.

172
00:18:50,967 --> 00:18:55,600
I also told them I was willing
to help them

173
00:18:55,767 --> 00:18:56,667
with the investigation.

174
00:18:56,800 --> 00:19:00,733
So they won't have a reason
to suspect me.

175
00:19:00,867 --> 00:19:04,367
Did Uncle Lucho hurt
a lot of people?

176
00:19:06,133 --> 00:19:08,533
You know what, dear.

177
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:12,300
You're Uncle Lucho
has his own world.

178
00:19:12,433 --> 00:19:17,567
And he hurt a lot of people.

179
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:18,967
But he...

180
00:19:21,767 --> 00:19:24,533
He was good to me.

181
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:33,100
He helped me up,
so I wouldn't lose hope.

182
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:40,933
Especially when I'd already
given up on life.

183
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:49,233
I will be grateful to him
all my life. But...

184
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:56,633
I can't accept the money
he left me.

185
00:19:56,767 --> 00:19:59,900
I can't use it.

186
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:03,133
What are you planning to do?

187
00:20:04,867 --> 00:20:11,900
I'll try to help the family
that he hurt.

188
00:20:12,033 --> 00:20:16,167
I will try to correct
all his wrongdoings,

189
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:18,767
even if he's already gone.

190
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,433
Just like you...

191
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:36,267
I also want to start a new life.

192
00:21:37,533 --> 00:21:44,200
Who would have thought
I would meet the woman

193
00:21:44,367 --> 00:21:46,767
I'd share the rest of my life
with on this island?

194
00:21:49,933 --> 00:21:53,500
I survived this island
because you were with me.

195
00:21:55,533 --> 00:21:59,700
And you taught me how to live.

196
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:05,133
The simple life
I've had with you

197
00:22:05,267 --> 00:22:07,867
is the happiest moment
of my life.

198
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:22,867
We'd been through a lot
before we got to this point.

199
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,267
We had a lot of problems.

200
00:22:27,033 --> 00:22:30,267
But with all those problems
we had,

201
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:32,800
I'm only sure of one thing.

202
00:22:38,333 --> 00:22:41,800
I love you so much,
Eden Sta. Maria.

203
00:22:44,067 --> 00:22:46,833
And I will love you for
the rest of my life.

204
00:22:53,133 --> 00:23:01,400
Red, thank you,
because you changed my life.

205
00:23:02,467 --> 00:23:08,033
I thought there was no place
for love in my life.

206
00:23:08,167 --> 00:23:11,433
Because I had a lot
of things to do.

207
00:23:11,567 --> 00:23:14,267
A lot of people depended on me.

208
00:23:15,467 --> 00:23:19,500
But when I met you on this
island...

209
00:23:19,633 --> 00:23:22,467
you taught me how to smile....

210
00:23:22,633 --> 00:23:25,167
to laugh.

211
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:32,500
You gave me a reason
to be happy.

212
00:23:34,267 --> 00:23:37,700
That's why I'm so grateful
to you, Red.

213
00:23:40,367 --> 00:23:43,333
I love you so much, too.

214
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:54,333
Each day I spend with you
is like being in paradise.
